instructions: Sign in to your Google Admin console . Sign in using your administrator account (does not end in @gmail.com). From the Admin console Home page, go to Devices . If you don't see Devices on the Home page, at the bottom, click More controls . On the left, click App management and then Manage apps for Android devices . Click Manage Whitelisted Apps . At the bottom, click Add . On the left, click Private apps .
